HEADWORD: Coaptation
<hw>Co`ap*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>coaptatio</ets>, fr. <ets>coaptare</ets> to fit together;
<ets>co-</ets> + <ets>aptare</ets>. See <er>Aptate</er>.]</ety> <def>The
adaptation or adjustment of parts to each other, as of a broken bone or
dislocated joint.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

